reviews.title: Soft Peach Sweater

Even so I would still recommend this sweater to anyone looking for a nice, soft, very pretty sweater.

reviews.title: Waffle Stitch Sweater
reviews.review_text: This a very comfortable sweater. It is thin, but keeps you warm. The downside is it has picks and some are too big to pull back through. I bought three. One for me and two for my daughters. One of my daughter's sweater had a very large pick (hole) in it. She is returning it. I am keeping mine as I could pull my picks back through.

reviews.title: Snagged but salvageable

The only reason I did not return it because of this is it is VERY comfortable. I should have taken pictures before I fixed it but did not.

reviews.title: Sweater.
reviews.review_text: Fits true to size, warm and soft to the touch. Not itchy although I wear a T-shirt underneath because I'm frequently cold . Bought in cream and red and have enjoyed immensely. Goes with leggings, jeans, trousers, Definitely recommend. One in each color you won't be sorry!

reviews.title: If I were you I'd pass on this one.
reviews.review_text: I'm so sorry to have to leave a negative comment about this beautiful sweater. I was so pleased when it arrived. Perfect fit, pretty color, soft and elegant looking and a great price. I wore it one time to the movies under a denim jean-type jacket. Maybe 4 hours? I didn't spill anything on it, snag it in any way, no opportunity for it to stretch out of shape...but, by the time we got home it was 2 sizes longer than when I put it on. Every part of the sweater that was covered by the jacket had threads pulled and snagged. Not just a few threads snagged, but dozens.I couldn't believe it. It was in such bad condition that I tossed it into the garbage.

The ladies waffle sweaters love them. I bought a white one before I just roll sleeves up otherwise perfect I bought the pink arms are long roll up sleeves I like it a little bit as I wear something underneath. I would get these sweaters again I'm allergic wool these are perfect.

reviews.title: TOOOO MANY PULLS!!!!!!!!!

I've already had 2 inch snags multiple times from pretty much nothing‚Ä¶ It's a piece of junk, no matter how warm and comfortable it is!

reviews.title: One Big Snag
reviews.review_text: The "quality" was not what I expected because this item, though it was clearly marked as a Clearance item on the website, arrived with a very LARGE - i.e. approximately 5 inches - snag in the right sleeve of the sweater. The yarn wasn't broken or cut, but it wasn't going to fit back into the waffle knit with a simple tug, either. Luckily, I crochet, so I used a small crochet hook to weave the snag back into the knit. I can clearly see where it was done, but most folks probably won't be able to identify the spot. Still...why would this item be shipped without notifying the customer of the flaw? I would have canceled the order if I had known I wasn't getting an intact item, even at the Clearance price. My local store had other colors of this sweater without the snag, and I would have happily chosen another color.
